Vaishampayana said Then King Yudhisthira addressed Nakula. O Madreya climb the tree and look in ten directions
Look at the water nearby and the trees resting on the water. O dear your brothers are tired and thirsty
Nakula said so and quickly climbed the tree. Looking at his elder brother from all sides he said
O king I see many trees resting on water There is no doubt that the ravens have no water
Then Satyadharti, Yudhisthira, the son of Kunti, said: O gentle one go at once and fetch water with your quivers
Nakula said so at the command of his elder brother He ran to wherever there was water and quickly reached it
He saw the clear water surrounded by cranes. Desiring to protect him he heard a voice from the sky
The yaksha said O dear child do not dare to do this former marriage O Madreya after answering your questions drink and take away
Ignoring his words Nakula became very thirsty He drank the cold water and fell down
Yudhisthira, the son of Kunti, was born in Nakula for a long time. He said to his heroic brother Sahadeva the subduer of enemies
Our brother Sahadeva born of your words has passed away for a long time Bring your brother and water in the same way
Sahadeva said so and returned in that direction. Then he beheld his brother Nakula killed on the ground
Tormented by grief for his brother and tormented by thirst Then he ran to the water and spoke to her
My dear son do not dare to do this former marriage Ask me questions and drink and take away as you please
Without taking that word Sahadeva became thirsty He drank the cold water and fell down
Then Yudhisthira, the son of Kunti, addressed Vijaya. O crusher of enemies your fearful brothers have been gone for a long time
Bring them both, good luck to you, and you bring water. O dear you are indeed the refuge of all of us who are in distress
Thus addressed Gudakesha took up his bow and arrows The intelligent Ravana with his sword loosened rushed towards that lake
Then the male tiger went to fetch water. Swetavahana saw the two brothers killed there
Seeing them as if they were asleep the lion among men was deeply grieved Raising his bow, Arjuna beheld the forest.
He saw nothing there in this great forest Exhausted Savyasachi ran for water
Then he heard a voice from the sky as he ran towards them What were you drinking that you can force it
O Kaunteya, if you will answer those questions I have asked. Then thou shalt drink water and take it away, O Arjuna.
