No confrontation should be made in the event of a general victory. O lord having subdued the enemy his purpose was attained by trust
After deliberation with the ministers and the great men who knew the mantras. Neglected and despised he was invincible at heart Then he should strike him at the right time with a slightly moving step Men who have achieved their goals should spoil the punishment for this
He who knows the beginning, the middle and the end should keep the hidden. Knowingly he should spoil his forces according to proof He should also infect with medicines by distinction and by giving them. It is not true that one should not like to associate with enemies in this way
Even if he looks for a long time he will kill the enemy Expect time to be spent so that they can gain confidence Victory is certain to be seen if it does not defeat the enemies immediately
He does not inflict surgery or cause wounds with his words When it is reached it does not strike in time nor does it turn around again O lord of the gods towards a man who desires to kill his enemies
For the man who passes by time is the eye of time. That time is again rare for him who wishes to perform his duties
And it should generate energy, collecting it, which is well-accepted. One should make a friend untimely and not harass him when he arrives
Abandoning lust and anger and also egoism. Engaged again and again he searched for the cave of the unfortunate
Gentleness, punishment, laziness and negligence, O best of the gods. O Indra wellplanned illusions deceive the unwise
Killing these four and setting them against the magic. Then he can strike the enemies without thinking
Whenever one can keep it secret one should do so Secretaries share secrets with one another
Or make it impossible and then move on to conversation with others. The fourfold Brahmadanda was not seen when seen
And discrimination should be applied first, and so should punishment in silence. The king should engage them at that particular time
At the right time he should bow down to the strongest of the enemies He was determined to kill him without hesitation
Speaking with bowing, giving and sweet words. One should serve even an enemy and never doubt him
Places and suspects should always be avoided. The king will not rest on his laurels when he is awake and rejected here
O best of the gods there is nothing more difficult than the opulence of various deeds
Similarly, it is said to be possible for various circles. One who strives, practicing Yoga, should think of friends and enemies.
