Indra said: What are the symptoms of the wicked, O best of the brahmins? When asked how can I know this is evil tell me
Brihaspati said: He who speaks of the indirect virtues is envious of the good virtues. He remains silent when others are praising him with his face turned towards others
Even in the absence of silence, it should be understood if there is no cause. Breathlessness, biting of the lips and shaking of the head.
He does frequently associated and speaks unconnected. Unseen he neither acts nor speaks in sight
He goes separately and eats together, not today as usual. Emotions should be noticed especially when sitting on a bed or in a carriage
Love in the night of suffering, dear, is such a characteristic of a friend. But the opposite should be understood, that is the characteristic of the enemy.
O lord of the heavens you should understand these things as they have been said The nature of corrupt men is stronger
O best of the gods this is the knowledge of the wicked O lord of the gods having heard the true meaning of the scriptures
Bhishma said: He, engaged in destroying the enemy, thus fulfilled the words of Brihaspati. Indra moved about in time for victory and brought the enemy under his control
Vaishampayana said: The brave men, armed with their armies and striking, went out of the city. When the sun sets the fish touch the three nets
They were triggers and fish and were enraged and mad about fighting. The mighty warriors greedy for the cows roared at one another
There were also frightening drunken elephants raised by their spears and goads They were ridden by skilled villagers like elephants
Their meeting was terrible tumultuous and iron furious O king let him enhance the kingdom of Yama kill one another O king there was no one equal to the gods and demons who rests on the sun He possessed infantry chariots elephants elephants horses riders and army
They attacked each other and killed each other The dust rose from the earth and something was perceived.
The birds fell to the ground covered with dust from the army The Sun disappeared with his arrows flying about
The space shone like a combination of pit lights. The bowmen's bows with golden backs were sprinkled with water Let the heroes of the world fall left and right Chariots followed by chariots and infantry followed by foot soldiers
There were great elephants on horseback and on horseback Swords footsteps spears shaktis and stomaras
O king they were enraged and killed each other in battle The valiant men armed with iron clubs struck each other in the battle
They could not turn the heroes in anger His upper lips were cut off his nose and his hair was cut off and he was not decorated He saw his head cut off and his earrings covered with dust His limbs were cut to pieces by the arrows and his body was invisible They looked like shawls and shoulders in the great battle of the kshatriyas His arms resembled those of serpents and were sprinkled with sandalwood paste The ground looks spread out with heads and earrings. A battle ensued between the charioteers
The horsemen and the horsemen of the infantry. The dust of the earth was covered with blood flowing
He became exhausted and behaved terribly without limits The Garudas sat down and were pierced deep by the arrows Their movement in the sky and their sight were obstructed Those brave creatures armed with spears fought each other in battle Enraged they could not turn the heroes away Shatanika killed a hundred and Vishalaksha killed four hundred The two mighty charioteers entered a huge army of trigartas
Both the strong and brave men entered the great army Keshakeshi the charioteer was very furious as they worshiped him
Noticing the three-horsemen they entered the chariot herd. Suryadatta in front and Madiraksha behind him
Virata killed five hundred chariots in the battle there He killed eight hundred horses and five great charioteers
The best of charioteers rode on various roads The golden chariot of Trigarta seized Susharma in the battle
The two great and mighty men were dealing there. They roared at each other like bulls in the cowsheds
Then king Susharma of the Trigartas who was mad about war The best among men (Dasaratha) arrived at the king in a two-chariot chariot
Then the two charioteers passed by in anger They quickly released their arrows like clouds streaming water
They were furious with each other Armed with sharp arrows they carried swords powerful clubs
Then the king struck Susharma with ten arrows He struck his four horses with five arrows
Similarly Susharma who was mad about fighting the king of fishes The connoisseur of supreme weapons struck him with fifty sharp arrows O great king the army of the king of fish Susharma They did not recognize each other then, covered with dust by the army
Sauti said Janamejaya, along with his brothers and sisters, Parikshit, is performing a long sacrifice at Kurukshetra. He had three brothers by Shrutasena. Ugrasena is Bhimasena. While they were engaged in that sacrifice Sarameya arrived
Struck by his brothers Janamejaya approached his mother crying
Grieving for her son the mother said to him who was crying 'Why are you crying? Who has struck you?'
He replied, 'I have been attacked by the brothers of Janamejaya.
His mother replied to him 'You have obviously committed an offense by which you have been struck down'
He said to her again, 'I have not offended you, I have not looked at anything, I have not offered sacrifices here.
Having heard this mother Sarama attended the sacrifice where Janamejaya along with his brothers was performing a long sacrifice
The angry woman said 'This son of mine has done nothing wrong he has not looked at the sacrificial offerings nor has he offered sacrifices Why has he been beaten'
When they said nothing she said to them 'Since this harmless man has been attacked you will be overcome with fear unseen'
