Haidimba is a mighty bird as strong as me O sinless one at your word let Ghatotkacha carry us all away
Vaishampayana said With the permission of the king of righteousness he remembered his son the demon Then righteous Ghatotkacha remembered his father
Then he stood up with folded hands and saluted the Pandavas. The mightyarmed Rama was greeted by the brahmins
He addressed his father Bhimasena who was of terrible prowess You remembered me and I have come to serve you at once
O mightyarmed one command me I shall undoubtedly do everything Having heard this Bhimasena embraced the demon
Bhishma said: This is your newly brought royal duties, O Yudhisthira. Venerable Brihaspati extols justice and righteousness
The venerable Vishalaksha and Kavya were great ascetics Sahasraksha and Mahendra and also Manu of Pracheta and also the venerable Bharadwaja and the sage Gaurashira. They were the pioneers of royal scriptures and were brahmins and eloquent in the Vedas
O best of the upholders of righteousness they praise protection alone O lotuseyed redeyed one listen to me about the means of kings
Charity and attention and charity at the right time out of envy Giving by logic and not giving by Yoga, O Yudhisthira. The collection of the virtuous, courage, dexterity, truth and the welfare of the people. Breaking the enemy's wings by unrighteousness and unrighteousness And how many of them are worn out and suffer from neglect. The use of two kinds of punishment is driven by time The abandonment of the names of the saints and the retention of the nobles. Hoarding and service to the hoarders, even to the wise. The delight of the strong and the constant observation of the people Distress in affairs and also enlargement of the treasury Distrust in the protection of the city: the breaking of the crowd of citizens. Properly looking after friends in the midst of enemies Upajapa and the visit of his servants to his city. Distrust in oneself and also in the consolation of others. Following morality and righteousness and always rising up. He should not disregard his enemies and always avoid ignoble things
For the rise of the kings was spoken of by Brihaspati. Listen to the verses about the root of royal duty
By rising nectar was obtained and by rising the demons were killed. By the rise of Indra I have attained excellence in heaven and in this world
A man who is a hero of upliftment overcomes the heroes of speech. They worship the heroes of the rise, the heroes of speech, delighting them.
Even a wise king is always without rise He is attackable to the enemies like a venomless snake
Nor should an enemy be ignored even by a weak one by a strong one Even a little poison burns and destroys a little
The enemy, even with one limb, took refuge in the fortress. It heats up the whole country even of a prosperous king
The king's secret is that the word is the gathering of the world for the sake of victory. Whatever is to be tolerated in his heart and whatever is caused by him And that his duty should be to hold the trouble with simplicity. He should perform righteous acts to humiliate the people
For the kingdom is a very great system and is not held by the selfless. It is not possible for a gentle man to carry this excellent place of illusion
The kingdom is held here by constant purity of all meat Therefore, O Yudhisthira, one should always live in a mixed manner.
Even if he is in trouble he is protecting his subjects That is also his extensive duty The kings behave in this way
I have described to you a trace of the duties of a king Tell me again, O best of the Kurus, wherein thou hast doubt.
Vaishampayana said Then Vyasa, the venerable Devasthana, and Ashma. Vasudeva, also Kripa, Satyaki and also Sanjaya. They were delighted as if they were being nurtured saying 'Well done well done' They also praised Bhishma the tiger among men the foremost among upholders of righteousness
Then, with a dejected mind, the foremost of the Kurus addressed Bhishma. With her eyes filled with tears she gently touched his feet O grandfather I shall ask you about my doubts tomorrow The Sun reaches the earth after drinking the auspicious taste
