Know me, Shalya, that I shall not go among those brave men. Betrayal of my friend is not to be tolerated; I shall give up my life and follow Drona.
There is no deliverance for the wise and the foolish at the end of life, for he who is honored by death. Therefore, O learned one, I shall pursue the sons of Partha; for it is not possible to deviate from my destiny.
My son was a king of extraordinary prowess who was always well behaved For the fulfillment of his objectives I give up my dear pleasures and my life which is difficult to give up
He wore tiger skin, cooing eyes, a golden tricolor, and a silver triple flute. Rama gave me this befitting gift
Looking at the pictures of bows, surgeons, flags, clubs, arrows and fierce forms. A blazing sword, the supreme weapon, and an auspicious conch, resounding fiercely.
