But when the armies of the Pandavas had withdrawn, O Bharatha. There were dreadful positions of the army in the battle
Then, O King, Bhagadatta, in the great battle, Ghatotkacha. Like a cloud covering a mountain he covered mount Meru with his arrows
The king killed the arrows that had fallen from the demon's bow In the battle Bhaimasena quickly struck him to the vital parts
He was beaten with many arrows with their wings bent The lord of demons was not disturbed like a mountain being split
He had fourteen astrologers and angry stomaras The demon sent them to the battle and cut them to pieces
The mightyarmed Hanuman cut them to pieces with his sharp arrows He also struck Bhagadatta with seven heron petals
