Thus having performed that worship, Pandava with his brothers. Indra rejoiced in that beautiful assembly like Indra in heaven
The sages are in the assembly with the Pandavas. Kings from various countries gathered there
Asita Devala Satya Sarpi Mali Mahashiras Arvavasu Sumitra Maitreya Sunaka and Bali The goat is a dalbhya, the thick-headed black dvaipayana is a parrot. Sumantu, Jaimini, Paila and also we are disciples of Vyasa. Tittiri and Yajnavalkya with their son Lomaharsana. Apsuhomya and Dhaumya were the sons of Animandavya and Kausika. Damoshnisha and Traibali are the leaves and the knees of the pot. Maunjayana, the eater of the wind, and Parasharya, the sarika. Balivaka, Sinivaka, Satyapala and the hardworking. There were jatukarnas and shikhavans and alambas and parijatakas The mountain is also the most fortunate and the great sage Markandeya. Savarna Bhaluki and Galva with holy hands Janghabandhu and Raibhya were the speed of anger and so was Bhrigu. The monkeys and the Kaundinyas are the eternal garlands of bees Kakshivan and Naushija and Nachiketa and Gautama. Paingya, Varaha, Sunaka and Śaṇḍilya, the great ascetics. The dog, the bamboo leg, the kalapa and the kadda. The ascetics were learned in dharma self-controlled and self-controlled
These and many others are well versed in the Vedas and Vedic literature. The foremost of ascetics worshiped the great soul in the assembly They were holy men who knew righteousness and were pure and immaculate telling stories In the same way the best of kshatriyas worship the king of righteousness
He was prosperous great righteous Munjaketu and enhancer The mighty Sangramajit Dumukha and Ugrasena Kakshasena, the lord of the earth, and Kshemaka, the invincible. The mighty Kamboja king Kamadda and Kampana The one who constantly shook the Yavanas. They were endowed with strength and courage armed with weapons and immeasurably valiant Just as god Vajradhara defeated the asuras of Kalakeya
Jatasura, king of the Madras, Kunti, and Pulinda, king of the Kirats. Similarly Angavanga with Pundraka and the kings of Pandyodra with Andhraka. Ango, Vanga, Sumitra, Saibya and Amitrakarshana. Sumana king of the Kirats and lord of the Yavanas Chanura, Devarata, Bhoja and Bhimaratha. Shrutayudha, Kalinga, Jayasena and Magadha. Sukarma and Chekitana and Pusswamitrakarshana. Then Ketuman Vasudeva and Vaideha were grateful The mighty Sudharma and Aniruddha and Shrutayu The king of Anupara is invincible and Sudarsana is the conqueror of succession Shishupala and his son and the king of Karusha. The princes of the Vrishnis were unassailable in the form of gods Ahuko and Vipruthu and Gada and Sarana. Akrura Kritavarma and Satyaka were the sons of Shini Then Bhishmaka, Akriti and the mighty Dhumatsena. Kekaya the great archer Yajnasena and Saumaki
The mighty Ketuman and Vasuman were armed with weapons These and many other kshatriyas are highly regarded We worshiped Yudhisthira, the son of Kunti, in the assembly. And those mighty princes who took refuge in Arjuna. They learned the art of archery dressed in fierce horses. O King the young sons of Vrishni were educated there
Raukmineya, Samba, Yuyudhana and Satyaki. Sudharma Aniruddha and Saibya the foremost among men
These and many other kings, O lord of the earth. Tumburu, the friend of Arjuna, used to reside here daily. Twenty-seven worship the great soul seated. Citrasena accompanied by his ministers gandharvas and apsaras They are skilled in song and music and are experts in harmony. Then the exhausted kinneras reached the place of dissolution Then they were stirred by the drums and the gandharvas. Those nobleminded men sing with divine tunes according to their righteousness They worship the sons of Pandu and also the sages, delighting them. There were men of good vows and truthful sitting in that assembly Like heaven the gods worship Brahma Yudhisthira.
