The mind, arising from egoism, is composed of the modes of nature. This third creation is called the egoistic.
O lord of men great beings arose from the mind Know this to be My opinion of the mind as the fourth creation.
Sound, touch, form, taste and smell. The thinkers of beings say that the fifth creation is material.
The eye, the tongue, and the sense of smell are the fifth. But it is said that the sixth creation is said to be composed of many thoughts.
O lord of men the sense organs of the ear arise from below It is said that this is the seventh creation; it is said to be of the senses.
O lord of men the ear and the skin arise upwards and the source arises obliquely It is said that this is the eighth creation and this is said to be upright.
O lord of men the oblique stream arises from the lower stream The wise say that this is the ninth creation, which is straightforward.
These are the nine creations and the elements, O lord of men. Twenty-four have been mentioned according to the evidence of the Vedas.
