 a curse saying 'You have chosen another priest; therefore your sacrifice has not been completed and you are about to be killed by an unprecedented Sattva'; by that curse Hiranyakasipu was killed. Then Visvaroopa, enhancing his mother's wings, became very austere and Indra engaged many beautiful apsaras to break his vow. Seeing them his mind was agitated and he soon became attached to them Having recognized him the apsaras said 'Let us go back as we came' Tvastra said to them Where are you going? Stay with me until all is well with you The women of the gods and the apsaras replied 'We pray to Indra the god of the gods who is the bestower of boons in the past' Then Visvaroopa said to them, "There will be no gods with Indra today." Then he chanted mantras and by those mantras Trisira grew up with one mouth in all the worlds as the brahmins performed ritualistic ceremonies in sacrifices. Those devatas along with Indra approached Brahma and said in the form of the universe In all sacrifices the moon is offered in sacrificial fire The moon is being drunk; Brahma said to them, 'The sage Bhrigu, Dadhīci, is performing austerities. Ask him for a boon; arrange for him to give up his body; let him be made a weapon with his bones. Then the gods came to the place where the venerable sage Dadhīci was performing austerities along with Indra They approached him in that manner and said, "O venerable one, his austerities are auspicious and indistinguishable. Dadhīca said to them: Welcome; tell me what to do; whatever you say I shall do. Then they told him that it was fitting for the venerable Rama to relinquish his body for the welfare of the world Then Dadhīci, likewise, undisturbed by pleasure and pain, oh, the great Yogi, having composed himself, gave up the body. When the bones of that Supreme Soul had fallen away, the creator seized them and made them into a thunderbolt. With that impenetrable and unassailable thunderbolt born of the bones of Brahma, entered by Visnu, Indra struck Visvaroopa and cut off his head. When that dual killing of a brahmin took place Indra out of fear abandoned the kingdom of the gods The cool lotus flower born in the waters entered the lotus flower flowing in the mind When the fear of killing Brahma was destroyed, the lord of the three worlds, Sachi, became the lord of the universe. Rajas and Tamas entered the gods The worlds became well-conquered. The devatas and sages consecrated Nahusha son of Ayusha in the kingdom of the gods and Hasha ruled the heavens with five hundred lights shining on his forehead destroying all his effulgence Then the worlds returned to their natural state and became healthy Then Nahusha said 'I have all eaten by Indra' Then Nahusha said to Indra I am sitting on the throne of Indra I have stolen the jewels of Indra's kingdom There is no unrighteousness in this you have enjoyed Indra's words She said to him I have some vows I have not decided I will come to you in that avabhrita in a few days' Then Sachi, afflicted with sorrow and grief, longing to see her husband, and seized by the fear of Nahusha, approached Brihaspati Having observed great rituals she called upon the goddess of fortune who bestowed boons with mantras and approached Sachi and said 'I am this you have invited me' What can I do to please you? Sachi bowed her head and said "O venerable one you deserve to show me my husband You are truthful and truthful" Then Indra, seeing her thin and threat, thought about it, Oh, my suffering, for I have lost my suffering, and when I seek my suffering, Indra said to her, “How does Nahusha call her away, and I will call her away. He entered the knot of seeds again
Then seeing Indra approaching Nahusha said to her 'The time has come' Sachi said to Indra as instructed Indra mounted the chariot driven by the great sages and approached Sachi
