The names are also secret and defined, O Bharatha. These things which have been described here by the sages have been related to you.
Thus I roam the earth in many different forms. And also, O Arjuna, the world of Brahma and the eternal world of the cows. I have protected you and you have won a great victory in battle
Whoever goes ahead of you when the battle is about to begin Know Him, O Rudra, O Arjuna, to be the God of the gods, the destroyer of the monkeys.
I have told you that time is the cause of anger He killed the same enemies you killed before.
That lord of the gods Umapati of immeasurable power Offer obeisances to that inexhaustible Lord of the universe, Lord of the universe.
And that which you have been told before and again and again is the conqueror of anger. The power of Him which thou hast heard at first, O Arjuna.
Narada said As soon as the noblemen recognized him the foremost among men The king of the ceremony touched the ground Yayati recovered from his fever and regained his divine abode
He was dressed in divine garlands and adorned with divine ornaments Endowed with divine fragrance his feet did not touch the earth
Then Vasumana shouted loudly in the past Then the renowned lord of charity Leki addressed the king
I have attained that which is deep in all the castes of the world I shall give you that too Please join me
The fruit of the charitable and the forgiving. And with whatever fruit I have obtained, may you be united with it.
Then Pratardana the foremost of the kshatriyas also spoke these words Just as he was always fond of righteousness and always devoted to war
I have attained fame in this world born of the Kshatriya dynasty You should be associated with him and the fruits of the words of a hero
The wise Shibiraushinara spoke in a sweet voice The same is true of young women who are playful
In battles, in falls, and in their troubles. I have never told you a lie before so go to heaven with that truth
O king it is like life and kingdom and the pleasures of desire I shall never abandon truth again; by that truth go to heaven.
As truth is my righteousness, so is truth my fire. Satakratu was pleased with that truth and went to heaven
Then there was Ashtaka the royal sage Kausika son of Madhavi The knower of righteousness reached Nahusha who had hundreds of fires
O lord my cows have been surrounded by hundreds of lotuses Receive the fruits of sacrifices performed by Vajapeya
I have no jewels, no money, no other clothes. Go to heaven with truthfulness which is not fit for sacrifices
As the daughters talked about the king In like manner the king left the earth and ascended to heaven
Thus all those kings were then honored with all their good deeds. The demons easily rescued him who had fallen into heaven
The daughters by their own righteousness by sacrifice and charity They were born in four royal dynasties and enhanced their families They ascended their highly intelligent grandfather to heaven
They said to the kings endowed with the virtues of royalty and all virtues of righteousness O king we are your daughters ascend to heaven
Cyavan said Take the boon from me and whatever doubt you have in your heart O best among men tell him I shall arrange everything for you
Kusika said: If you are pleased, O Lord, then tell me, O Bhrigu. I wish to hear the reason why you have stayed at my house
Bed and onepaāna for twenty-one days. The foremost of ascetics said nothing and went outside
Disappearing and suddenly seeing again. O brahmin I lay down again for twenty one days
Walking and eating at my house when I was anointed with oil They brought various kinds of food which had been burnt by the blazing fire
And the sudden departure in the chariot which you have done. Seeing the disposal of wealth and the forest
O great sage there were many golden palaces Seeing the footprints of the merchants and coral trees
I wish to hear the reason for his absence again O best of the Bhrigus I am very much perplexed thinking about this
I cannot find a determination of all this here O ascetic I wish to hear the truth about my duty
Cyavan said Listen in full to what this is and for what reason. O king it is not possible not to tell you when asked in this way
While my grandfather was speaking in the past in the assembly of the gods O king listen to me tell you what I have heard
There will be a hybridization of clans by the opposition of Brahmins and Kshatriyas. O king you will have a grandson endowed with splendor and valor
Then I came to you to destroy your clan. With the intention of cutting off Kushika they want to burn your dynasty
Then I came to the city and told you, O king. I shall obtain some regulation Please render service
I have not found anything wrong with you at home O saintly king by that you are living You would not have been otherwise
Thus he resolved for twenty-one days. O king if anyone can wake me up I am asleep
When you and your wife fell asleep and did not wake you up O best of kings I was very much pleased with your mind
"O king if you will let me go I shall get up and leave If you ask me where you are going I swear to you 'O lord'
I disappeared and again and again in your house. Having practiced yoga he fell asleep for twenty-one days.
Whether you are hungry or tired you will envy me, O lord of men. Having thus resolved I have exhausted you both from hunger
O king there was not even the slightest anger in your mind O best among men I am pleased with your wife
I brought food and lit it If you are angry out of envy I am angry with you
Then I got into the chariot and spoke to you, O king. Your wife told me to get rid of you and you did so O lord of men I am undoubtedly pleased with him Even when you gave up your wealth anger did not overtake you
Then, O king, you were pleased to do this again. O lord of men know that the forest belongs to his wife again
For your pleasure this consciousness has made me see heaven O king whatever you have seen in this forest is a divine proof
O king you have a golden objective with your body O best of kings he and his wife experienced him for a moment
O lord of men to demonstrate his austerities and righteousness O king I also know the desire which was there
O lord of the earth you are a brahmin and an ascetic O king despising his status as king of men and lord of gods
O dear brahminhood is rarely attained She was ascetic in the presence of a brahmin and ascetic
This will be your desire from Kushika, a Kausika brahmin. The third man will attain to you the status of a brahmin
O best of the earth your lineage is by the splendor of the Bhrigus Your grandson will be an ascetic and effulgent like fire
who will cause fear to gods and men. I tell you the truth about the three worlds alone
Rajarshi what is on your mind. I shall go on a pilgrimage to a holy place long ago Time is running out
Kusika said O great sage this is the very boon I have received today which has pleased you O sinless one let this be so that you may become my grandson Take the gift
O venerable one let brahminhood be my boon to my family O venerable one I wish to tell you again in detail
How will my family come to be a brahmin, O son of Bhrigu? Who will be my friend and who will be my friend
Vaishampayana said Thus addressed, O great king, Kunti addressed Pandu. Then he saw the heroic lord of the earth the bull among the Kurus
O knower of dharma it is not proper for you to speak thus to me who am devoted to you O lotuseyed wife of dharma
But you alone, O mighty-armed one, have children in me, O Bharatha. O valiant one you will beget children endowed with prowess according to righteousness
O tiger among men I shall go to heaven with you And go thou alone, O descendant of the Kurus, to me for a son.
I would not go to any other man except you even in my mind. Who else on earth is superior to you
And in the meantime, O righteous one, listen to this ancient story from me. O largeeyed one I shall recite this wellknown story
The king became famous as Vyushitasva In the past he was supremely righteous and enhanced the dynasty of Puru
And while the righteous mightyarmed Rama was performing the sacrifice Then Indra along with divine sages arrived
Indra was satisfied with the moon and the brahmins with alms Then at the sacrifice of the great royal sage Vyushitasva Then the gods and brahmarshis performed the rituals themselves O king thereafter the horse of Vyushita shone brightly
It is like heat to all beings at the end of winter That excellent king conquered and captured kings He drove them from the east to the north, from the west to the south. The mighty Vyushitasva performed the great sacrifice of Asvamedha
He became the king with the strength of ten serpents Even those who are well versed in the Puranas sing stories here O best of the Kurus, O lord of men, aged in fame, on a horse that has been destroyed. Having conquered this earth by riding his horse on the seashore A father raised his sons of all castes The performer of sacrifices bestowed wealth on brahmins by performing great sacrifices
Then he took the gems and stole the great sacrifices She also gave birth to many moons and those who were in the moon's position
He had a highly respected wife named Kakshivati O lord of men there is a woman named Bhadra who is unparalleled in beauty on earth
It is said that they desired each other Full of lust he was afflicted with tuberculosis In that short time he disappeared like the sun setting When the lord of men died his wife was deeply grieved
O tiger among men we have heard that she is crying without a son O lord of men Bhadra is in great distress Listen to that
Bhadra said A woman knower of supreme righteousness is deprived of her husband A woman who does not live without her husband lives in misery
O best of kshatriyas it is better for a woman to die without her husband I wish to go to your place Please take me away I can't live without you for a moment. O king be kind to me and take me away at once
I will follow behind you on even and uneven ground O tiger among men I am going to turn you away
O king she followed him like a shadow and was always subdued O tiger among men I shall always be devoted to the welfare of my dear ones
From today onwards, O king, I am suffering from heartache. O lotus-eyed one the troubles will overwhelm you without you
Unfortunately I must have separated from my companions That is why my separation from you has come upon me
But a woman who is separated from her husband lives even for a moment O king that sinful lady is living in misery like hell
I have made them united and separated in my former body That which is accumulated in the former bodies by sinful actions. O king the grief caused by your separation has overtaken me O king from today onwards I shall lie down on a mat of kusha grass Devoted to seeing you I shall be filled with happiness
Show me, O tiger among men, and instruct me to be happy. O lord of men she lamented piteously
Kunyu said thus in many ways to her again and again while she was crying. Embracing the corpse her voice disappeared and spoke
"O gentle lady get up and go I shall give you your boon here O lady with a beautiful smile I shall beget children
I spent the fourteenth day in my own beautiful bed On the eighth day you should take a bath in the season and lie down with me
Thus advised the chaste goddess did so Then Bhadra asked for a son as he had said
O best of the Bharatas that goddess gave birth to that corpse O best of the Bharatas three Salvas and four Madras sons
So also, O best of the Bharatas, with such a mind in Me. Endowed with the power of asceticism and yoga he is capable of begetting sons
Vaiśampāyana said: When the ten-armed Yudhisthira and Bhimasena and Arjuna had departed. Yama and Krishna and the priest saw expensive chariots fitted with excellent horses The heroes, the lights of the lord of the ghosts, set out for the forest together. He gave them gold coins clothes and cows and learned the letters and mantras.
The messengers were sent to the city with twenty weapons bows weapons and arrows burning The Mauryas and the evening men took their instruments and went down to the lower regions
Then they gave the princess clothes nurses maids and ornaments Indrasena at once seized the chariot and rode towards the lower part of the body
Then the wretched citizens approached the best of the Kurus and circumambulated him All the brahmins and chiefs of the Kurus and Jadulas were pleased and addressed him
Pleased with them the king of righteousness along with the bearers addressed them The great soul king (Dasaratha) stood there seeing the crowd of people of the Kurus and the forests
The great chief of the Kurus treated them like a father treats his sons Then Bharata's eminent sons became like their father's sons
Then the great crowds of people approached him and stood around the hero of the Kurus. O King all of them were frightened and cried out 'Alas my lord alas irreligion' with tears in their eyes
The best is the king of the Kurus, and he is like a father to the people, leaving us behind his sons. Where has the king of righteousness gone leaving behind all the inhabitants of Janapada
Woe to Dhritarashtra, the cruel-minded, woe to Saubala, the sinful-minded Karna. O king sinful men desire misfortune for you who are ever virtuous
The great soul himself settled in an incomparable city like the city of Mahadeva Where has the king of righteousness gone leaving the sacrificial ground of immeasurable deeds
The great soul Mayo made the assembly like the night, shining like the assembly of the gods. Where has the king of righteousness gone leaving behind that illusory energy like the protector of gods
The best of the knowers of dharma, kama and artha addressed them with a terrible loud voice. The king will take residence in the forests and gain the fame of his enemies
You have reached the chiefs of the brahmins together and separately with the ascetics He who is persuasive and conversant with righteousness and artha attains supreme perfection in truthfulness of speech
Thus addressed by Arjuna, the Brahmanas and all castes, O King. With joyful greetings they circumambulated the foremost of the upholders of righteousness they
Inviting Partha, Vrikodara, Arjuna, Yajnasena and Yama. With Yudhisthira's permission they set out for the kingdom devoid of joy
The Supreme Personality of Godhead said: Inquiring into the nature, I have spoken this out of love. Neither by reproach nor by wisdom nor by anger nor by discrimination.
I know your greatness and what strength you know. Or does he know your actions? I do not defeat you.
And as thou, O Pandava, thinkest well of thyself. I meditate on you even a thousandfold
And in what kind of family he was born and worshiped by all the kings. O Bhima you are such a friend and wellwisher
O Bhima inquiring about doubtful righteousness Men do not determine the alternative between gods and men.
For he is the cause of the fulfillment of the purposes of man. Even at his destruction his manliness is doubtful
Otherwise they have been viewed by poets who see faults Otherwise they would rotate like speeds in the sky
It was well-advised and well-advised and justly arranged. The embryo created by human beings is sustained even by destiny
Even destiny is thwarted by manliness Cold and heat, and also rain, in hunger and thirst, O Arjuna.
Whatever else is done by a man of destiny himself Therefore there is also a sign of non-contradiction.
There is no other instinct of the world, O Pandavas, than action. If thus the intellect acts, there will be fruit in both.
He who thus has made up his mind is engaged in his own actions. He who is not perfect is not distressed, nor does he rejoice in perfection.
There is this inference defined to me by Bhimasena. No ultimate success should be said in a battle with the enemy.
There would be no very devoid rays and in the opposite of being. I tell you this for the sake of cutting off depression or even depression
The next day, O Pandava, he reached the presence of Dhritarashtra. I shall endeavor to appease you for your great sake
If they will make peace, then I will have infinite fame. Your desire has been fulfilled and their welfare is excellent
If they are observed they will not obey my words The battle of the Kurus will be a terrible task
Bhimasena has placed the burden on you in this battle The dust should be carried by Arjuna and others should be carried.
I will be a terrible controller in battle This is Arjuna's desire I do not desire war
Therefore I doubt, O Bhiksha, that your splendor is equal to that of fire when you speak in a clumsy manner.
Shaunaka said: My dear father studied the entire Purana in the past. O Laumaharshana I hope you have understood all that
For in the Puranas there are divine stories and the original dynasties of the wise. We have heard these stories from your father in the past
and then I. I would like to hear about the lineage of Bhrigu first Tell us this story We are fortunate to hear it from you
Sauti said that which was thoroughly studied in the past by the best of the great brahmins. As described by the brahmins of Vaishampayana
Listen carefully to what my father taught me by the gods Indra the sages and the Maruts Bhrigu, the son of Bhrigu, is worshiped by the noble dynasty. O great sage I formerly belonged to this dynasty of yours Bhrigu
I shall tell you as it is properly based on the ancients The venerable great sage Bhrigu was created by the selfborn Brahma We have heard that he was born from fire in the sacrifice of Varuna Bhrigu had a very beloved son named Cyavana
Cyavan's father-in-law was a righteous man named Pramati Pramati also had a son named Ruru by the wife of Ghritachi
Ruru also had a son named Shunaka who was well versed in the Vedas Your righteous great-grandfather was born to the best of women
He was ascetic and illustrious and wellversed in the Vedas He was righteous truthful and self-controlled and kept his diet under control
Saunaka said O son of Suta as it was with that great Bhrigu I am asking you to tell me about your renowned Cyavana status
Sauti said Puloma the beloved wife of Bhrigu A pregnancy born of the prowess of Bhrigu was born to her
Then, O best of the Bhrigus, Puloma was born in that womb. At the appointed time he married a renowned righteous wife of equal character Bhrigu the best of the upholders of righteousness set out for his consecration Then the rakshasa approached Puloma's hermitage
He entered the hermitage and saw the irreproachable wife of Bhrigu Overwhelmed with desire he fainted
The beautiful Puloma the rakshasa arrived Then he invited them with wild fruits and roots
O Brahman the demon then tormented her with his heart's desire O king he was delighted to see her and wanted to take her away
Desiring to take away the auspicious task he said it was done That lady with a pure smile had been engaged by Pulomna in the past
His father later gave her to Bhrigu in accordance with the scriptures O descendant of Bhrigu that sin is ever present in his heart
Then he thought to himself 'This is the gap' Then he beheld a blazing fire burning in the shelter of the fire
Then the demon asked him about the fire burning O fire I ask you truthfully tell me whose wife she is
You are the face of the gods, tell me, asks the fire. I chose this fair complexioned lady for my wife earlier
Later his father, who was a liar, gave her to the cow. If this beautiful lady is the wife of Bhrigu she has gone away in seclusion
"Tell me the truth I wish to take away this hermitage Samanyu remains there as if burning his heart If Bhrigu obtained this slenderwaisted wife of mine before me
Sauti said thus inviting the demon to the burning fire. Doubtful he again and again inquired of Bhrigu's wife
Tvamagne! You move within all beings at all times. Tell the poet the truth about pious and sinful things as a witness
My wife was abducted by Bhrigu who was a liar before me If this is so you should tell me the truth
On hearing from you I shall abduct the wife of Bhrigu from this hermitage Tell me the truth while you are watching the fire burn
Sauti said, "On hearing these words of his, Saptachi was grieved. Frightened by the lie and the curse of Bhrigu he said slowly
Agni said O delight of the demons you chose Pulomeya in the past Why did you choose this forest of mantras in the past according to tradition
My father gave this illustrious Pulomeya to Bhrigu Greedy for a boon your illustrious father will not give it to you
Therefore, by the action seen in the Vedas, according to the ritual. O demon sage Gu got his wife with me in front of him
I understand that she is I do not wish to lie O best of demons lies are not always worshiped in this world
Narada said This is a great and excellent city known as Hiranyapura. There were hundreds of demons and giants who wandered about by illusory powers
It was built by Visvakarma with no small effort It was created by my mind and resided in the nether world
Here are thousands of illusory powers transforming the mighty. In the past there lived valiant demons who had been granted boons
These are not by Indra or by any other Yama or Varuna. They can be brought under control as well as by wealth.4!
The asuras and the Kalakhanjas also born of the feet of Visnu. The southwestern demons born of the feet of Brahma They had fangs and were terribly fast and mighty like the wind Endowed with the power of magic they live here in Matala
The demons called Nivatakavachas were mad about war You know how Indra cannot hinder him
Many times you and your son are drunk and cow-faced. The king of the gods and husband of Sachi along with his son were defeated
Look at the golden and silver houses in Matala They were attained by action in accordance with rituals
They were painted with emeralds and beautiful corals They were white like the sun and crystal and shone like diamonds
They looked like earth and were made of lotuses They looked like mountains and even like forests
They looked like the sun and looked like blazing fire They were tall and dense and decorated with a network of gems
These cannot be specified in form or substance. They are also perfect in virtue and have the virtue of proof.
Look at the games of the demons and also at their beds Expensive vessels and seats are moving about
There were clouds and mountains and streams of water They also saw trees with flowers and fruits at will
Someone here in Matale would be a nice boon to you. Or else if you think so let us go to the other side of the earth
Matali replied to him while he was speaking in such a manner O divine sage do not cause me displeasure to the inhabitants of heaven
For brothers gods and demons are always attached to enmity. How can I enjoy a relationship with the other party
Let us go elsewhere well I do not deserve to see the demons I know yourself and your violent mind
Markandeya said to Skanda, who was seated, wearing a garland of golden shields. He wore a golden crest and a crown with golden eyes and great effulgence
He was dressed in red and had sharp teeth and was delightful. Endowed with all virtues it is very dear even to the three worlds
Then he saw the boon-giving brave young man with polished earrings. The lotus-like goddess of fortune, embodied in herself, worshiped him.
Then the best of young men was endowed with prosperity and fame He is seen by all beings seated like the Moon on the full moon
The great brahmins worshiped that mighty warrior Then also the great sages there said this to Skanda.
The sages said: Hiranyagarbha, may you be blessed and become Lord Shankara of the worlds. Born of six kings you have subdued all the worlds
O best of the gods you have granted them safety therefore you are Indra fearless to the three worlds
Skanda said What is Indra doing here for all the worlds, O ascetics? How does Lord of the gods ever protect hosts of gods
The sages said: Indra gives strength, splendor and happiness to the beings. Thus satisfied the lord of the gods grants all his desires
He withdraws the wicked and bestows the vows. The destroyer of Bala disciplines all beings in their duties The Sun will be in the non-Sun and the Moon in the Moon. Fire and wind and the waters of the earth are produced by causes. This is what Indra should do for Indra has immense strength. O valiant one you are the most powerful and mighty therefore become Indra for us
Indra said O mightyarmed Indra may you be the source of happiness for all of us O best of men get yourself consecrated today You have attained your form
Skanda said: Rule thou the three worlds, unspeakable, engaged in victory. O Indra I am your servant I do not desire to become Indra
Indra said Your strength is wonderful O valiant one kill the gods and enemies Astonished at your prowess the worlds will despise me
O valiant one who remained as Indra was defeated without strength They will tirelessly try to separate us from each other And when you are pierced, O Lord, the world will come to a duality. And so it is with us in the fixed worlds divided into two parts
Vichaha will begin to distinguish between beings, O mighty one. O dear you will conquer me in battle according to your faith Therefore do not think that you will become Indra
Skanda said Thou alone art the king May all good be to thee and to me in the three worlds. O Indra tell me what I shall do and what you command
Indra said O mighty one on your words I shall become Indra If you have spoken this statement with certainty Or if you wish to command me, O Skanda, listen to me. Consecrate yourself as the mighty commander of the army of the gods
Skanda said: For the destruction of the demons and the fulfillment of the objectives of the gods. Consecrate me as commander of the army for the welfare of cows and brahmins
Markandeya said He was consecrated by Indra along with all the hosts of gods He shone very brightly there worshiped by the great sages. The golden umbrella he was carrying shone brightly Just as the self-circle of a well-burnt fire.
His divine golden necklace was made by Visvakarma She was bound by the illustrious destroyer of Tripura himself O tiger among men O scorcher of enemies arrive with the goddess
The venerable cow and bull flag worshiped him with great pleasure The brahmins called Rudra Agni and thereafter he became the son of Rudra
Rudra released Venus and it became a white mountain. The senses of the fire were turned into white by the krittikas on the mountain
All the devatas saw him being worshiped by Rudra Then they addressed Guha the son of Rudra as the best of virtuous men
This child was born by Rudra after entering the fire Then Skanda the son of Rudra was born there
The fire of Rudra is the fire of Svaha and the six women, O Bharatha. From him was born Skanda the best of the gods the son of Rudra
The son of Pavaka was dressed in red clothes His glorious body shines like the Sun with red clouds
The chicken was given to him by the fire and his flag was decorated. It looked like the red fire of death raised on the chariot
That action which is the light, peace and strength of all beings. That power of Achata enhances the victory of the gods
The shield entered his body and was easy. That always appears to the god while he is fighting. Power, righteousness, strength, splendour, loveliness, truth, and elevation. Brahmanism, freedom from delusion, protection of the devotees. and the destruction of enemies and the protection of the worlds. O lord of men all these were born with Skanda
Thus all the hosts of gods consecrated him and adorned him The orb of the full Moon looked like a cluster of flowers
with the desired sounds of study and the best of the gods' trumpets. The songs of gods gandharvas and hosts of apsaras were heard
These and many others were well adorned and satisfied and happy. He was well surrounded by hosts of devils and gods Then Pavaki appears to be playing and is anointed by the gods. The devatas beheld the great army installed The darkness killed the sun as it rose here. Then all the armies of the gods in their thousands approached him
All directions are crying out 'You are our husband' The venerable Lord surrounded by hosts of all beings reached them He was worshiped and praised and consoled them too. Then Satakratu the commander of the army consecrated Skanda
He remembered the army of the gods whom he had delivered Surely this husband of hers was ordained by Brahma himself Thinking about it he brought the decorated army of the gods O best of the gods this maiden Balabhidiya said to Skanda When you were born, you were designated as your wife by Svayambhuva. Therefore you should hold her hand in accordance with rituals followed by mantras Take the right hand of the goddess with the effulgence of a lotus Thus addressed he licked her hand in accordance with tradition
Brihaspati, knowing the mantras, chanted and offered sacrifices. Thus men know Devasena as the queen of Skanda
The sixth, which the Brahmins call Lakshmi, hope and bestower of happiness. Sinivali and Kuhu with their livelihoods were invincible
When Skanda was obtained as his eternal husband by the army of the gods Then goddess Lakshmi herself incarnate took refuge in him Sri Jushta is the fifth Skanda, hence Sri Panchami is called. Since the great guest was fulfilled on the sixth day
Having offered obeisances to Narayana and Nara the best of men Then goddess Saraswati should chant Jaya to Vyasa.
Janamejaya said Thus hearing of the battle of Mausal in the Vrishni and Andhaka dynasty. What did the Pandavas do when Krishna thus ascended to heaven?
Vaishampayana said Having thus heard the great slaughter of the Vrishnis, king of the Kurus. Fixing his mind on his departure he addressed Arjuna O great soul time cooks all beings I think you too should see the noose of death
Thus addressed, Kaunteya said, "Time is time. He followed the advice of his wise elder brother
Knowing the opinion of Arjuna, Bhimasena and Yama. They followed the words spoken by Savyasachi
Then he brought Yuyutsumana and went away for the sake of righteousness Yudhisthira bestowed the entire kingdom on the son of a vaisya
He was crowned in his kingdom and tested as a king. Then said king Subhadra the elder brother of the Pandavas in grief This is your son's son who will be the king of the Kurus. The remainder of the Yadus Vajra was made king
The Yadavas were scattered in Astinapura and Indraprastha You should protect king Vajra and do not set your mind on irreligion
Having said this the king of righteousness addressed the wise Vasudeva The same was true of the aged maternal uncle Rama and others The righteous Rama along with his brothers offered water without laziness and performed shraddha rituals for all of them in accordance with tradition
Dvaipayana and Narada and Markandeya, the rich in asceticism. Bharadwaja and Yajnavalkya made an effort to address Hari
He fed them delicious food and chanted the hymns of Shangina He gave them gems clothes villages horses and chariots Then hundreds of thousands of women from the chief brahmins Then he paid homage to the preceptor Kripa who was honored by the citizens The best of Bharatas gave him his disciple Parikshit. Then Yudhisthira brought all his subjects together.
The royal sage told him everything he intended to do On hearing his words the inhabitants of the city rejoiced They were greatly agitated and did not rejoice at his words Then they told the king that this should not be done
The king, who knew the laws of the alternation of time, did not do so. Then the righteous Rama persuaded the inhabitants of the towns and villages
Then he decided to leave after commanding his brother Then king Yudhisthira son of Dharma of the Kurus appeared She threw away her ornaments and took up her bark garments Bhima and Arjuna and also the illustrious Draupadi. In the same way, O king, all of them took the bark. Having performed the sacrifice in accordance with tradition, O best of the Bharatas, she is faithful. All the leading men released the fires into the water and set out Then all the women wept at the sight of the noble men
They set out like the sixth Draupadi who had won a gamble in the past. All the brothers were delighted at their departure
Knowing the opinion of Yudhisthira and observing the destruction of the Vrishnis. There were five brothers Krishna the sixth and Sva the seventh The seventh king set out from Gajasahvaya by himself The citizens and all the inner palaces followed him at a distance
No one could tell him to stop. Then all the men of the city turned away
Kripa and others also surrounded Yuyutsu. O son of the Kurus Ulupi the daughter of the serpent entered Ganga
Chitrangada also went to Manipurapura Other mothers who were learned surrounded Parikshita
The great Pandavas and the illustrious Draupadi. O son of the Kurus having observed a fast they set out from there in the forefront
Great souls endowed with Yoga have attained the Dharma of renunciation. They reached many countries rivers and seas
Yudhisthira went first and Bhima followed. Arjuna and also Yama followed him in order. Behind him was a beautiful dark lady with lotus eyes O best of the Bharatas Draupadi the best among women departed
The dog also followed the Pandavas alone as they set out for the forest. The heroes gradually reached the ocean of waters of Lohitya
