O great king Valakhilya and Ashmakutta were ascetics Others used toothpicks and mortars and others innumerable They are ascetics who eat air and water and eat leaves They also lay on the ground observing various rituals There were sages there near the river Saraswati The celestials beautified the best of rivers like Ganga
Hundreds of sages and sacrificers assembled The highly vowed men saw no opportunity for Saraswati
Then they constructed that holy place with sacred veils They offered sacrifices in the fire and performed various rituals
Then the dark assembly of sages was filled with despair and anxiety O best of kings for their sake Saraswati showed them
Then Saraswati withdrew after making many flowers O Janamejaya, show mercy to the sages who perform pious austerities.
O best of kings Saraswati then turned away for their sake Again the best of rivers flowed facing west Having made an infallible journey I shall go back to them O king the great river performed a wonderful feat
Thus, O king, that Kunja is known as Naimishiya. O best of the Kurus perform a great ritual in Kurukshetra There I saw many flowers and the river Saraswati had withdrawn Then great Rama was astonished
The delight of the Yadus took his bath there as per ritual Giving gifts to the brahmins and various vessels 59 and distributing foodstuffs of various kinds to the brahmins O King worshiped by brahmins Bala then departed It is the best of Saraswati holy places and is home to various birds. Balareṅgudakaśmaryaplakṣaśvatthabibhitaka trees There were conch shells palm trees curry trees and yellow trees There were trees of various kinds in the holy places of Saraswati
Karushakavara and bilva and ramrataka trees. It was decorated with very loose buds and parijatas
It is beautiful with many banana forests Even with wind water fruits leaves teeth and mortars It was also surrounded by many sages with stone mounds and forests It was crowded with hundreds of herds of deer resounding with the sound of their studies
It is served by non-violent men for the sake of the supreme righteousness. Halayudha reached the holy place known as Saptasarasvata The great sage Siddha Makunaka performed austerities there
Vaishampayana said Yudhisthira, having been consecrated and having attained the kingdom, having attained great wisdom. O son of Dasarha purified with folded palms addressed the lotus-eyed Lord By Thy grace, O Krishna, by Thy law and by Thy strength. O tiger among the Yadus by your intellect and prowess I have regained this kingdom of my forefathers "O lotus-eyed subduer of enemies I salute you again and again
They call Thee alone the Purusha; they call Thee the Lord of the Sattvas. The attentive brahmins praise you by various names
O Visvakarma, I offer my obeisances unto Thee, O Soul of the universe, O origin of the universe. Vishnu, Jisnu, Hare, Krishna, Vaikuntha, the Supreme Person.
You, the old Aditi, have become pregnant in seven parts. Thou alone art the womb of Prishni, even though they say that Thou art the three ages.
Shuchisrava, Hrishikesha, is called Ghritahinsa. Thou art the three-eyed Sambhu alone, the almighty and also Damodara.
The boar is characterized by fire, the great sun, the bull and the star. He was a man of great courage and mighty in a ship
The senior Ugrasenani: Satya Vajasanirguha. Acyuta, the deformed bull of the enemies, is sanctified.
You are the black dharma, the original bull-darbha, the bull-monkey. The sea of ​​irreligion, the three-cupped, the three-fold, the three-dimensional, the fallen from the heavens.
The Emperor, the Cosmic, and the Svarat, the King of the gods, are born of Bhava. You are the almighty, all-powerful, all-powerful, all-kṛṣṇa, all-kṛṣṇa-varmā.
You are Kapila, the physician who makes the sacrificial offerings, and Vamana. Thou art called Yajna, Dhruva, Patanga and Yajnasena.
Shikhandi, Nahusha, Babhru, touch the heavens, and thou art Punarvasu. There were also Rukmayajna Sushena and Dundubhi
Gabhastinemi, Sripadya, Pushkara, holds flowers. Ribhu, the almighty, the all-subtle, and also the character, Thou readest.
Thou art the treasure of waters, Thou art Brahma, Thou art the holy abode, the knower of the abode. They call Thee Hiranyagarbha, Svadha and Svaha, O Kesava.
Thou art the womb and the annihilation of this, O Krishna, Thou alone createst this universe before. And this universe is under Thy control, O father of the universe. Obeisance unto Thee, wielder of the ink, wheel and sword.
Thus praised by the king of righteousness, Krishna, the lotus-eyed, was pleased in the midst of the assembly. The Yadavas greeted Bharata, the foremost of the Pandavas, with abundant words.
